  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A UK prospective, single-centre feasibility study investigating the effects of exercise
      therapy on functional capacity in patients on the waiting list for liver transplantation.
      Patients will receive a 12-week home prehabilitation program (daily step program; functional
      resistance exercise sessions; telephone health call or virtual clinic). The following will be
      assessed at weeks 0, 6 and 12 weeks: feasibility (recruitment, compliance, safety, patients
      perception), functional capacity (ISWT, SPBT), psychological wellbeing (HADS questionnaire)
      and quality of life (EQ-5D)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
